WEBVTT

00:00.039 --> 00:01.039
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

00:03.702 --> 00:05.803
Mike, your father's coming over now.

00:05.828 --> 00:07.061
This is the perfect time to ask him.

00:07.063 --> 00:09.930
Why do you always want us to connect?

00:09.932 --> 00:13.834
Can I just run out the
clock until he dies?

00:13.836 --> 00:15.536
You and your dad have
been getting closer,

00:15.538 --> 00:17.037
so let's keep that going.

00:17.039 --> 00:18.339
- Here he comes.
- Stop it, stop it, stop it.

00:18.341 --> 00:19.740
He's almost here. Don't be nervous.

00:19.742 --> 00:20.808
- Dad, hey.
- Hi.

00:20.810 --> 00:24.045
It's game night. You wanna be partners?

00:24.047 --> 00:26.380
- Sure, why not?
- Really?

00:26.382 --> 00:30.751
Thanks. I mean, I don't care.

00:30.753 --> 00:32.485
It doesn't matter who
your partner is, Dad.

00:32.488 --> 00:34.221
Stella and I always win.

00:34.223 --> 00:35.222
You know, now that you're adults,

00:35.224 --> 00:37.425
I think you can handle the truth.

00:37.427 --> 00:38.759
We always let you win.

00:38.761 --> 00:39.994
What?

00:39.996 --> 00:41.695
- You let us win?
- Don't be upset.

00:41.697 --> 00:43.531
We were just trying to
bolster your self-esteem.

00:43.533 --> 00:46.600
Not a parent's job.

00:46.602 --> 00:50.004
With all the non-stop praise and
trophies for just showing up

00:50.006 --> 00:53.407
your generation can't handle losing.

00:53.409 --> 00:55.676
I don't want to win
without actually winning.

00:55.678 --> 00:59.547
Stella, we're gonna win tonight,
on our own, fair and square.

00:59.549 --> 01:01.215
Yeah!

01:01.217 --> 01:04.084
If we're losing, let us win.

01:04.087 --> 01:05.953
Are you kidding? We're
going to crush 'em.

01:05.955 --> 01:07.455
Right, partner?

01:07.457 --> 01:09.256
Oh, I forgot the damn ketchup.

01:09.258 --> 01:11.992
I'll get it for you...

01:11.994 --> 01:14.895
partner.

01:14.897 --> 01:16.897
- Bob.
- Hey, Alice.

01:16.899 --> 01:20.000
I have a big surprise for you.

01:20.002 --> 01:22.536
- Ethan!
- Hey, Dad!

01:22.538 --> 01:24.839
Hey!

01:24.841 --> 01:27.675
Everyone, it's Alice's boy, Ethan,

01:27.677 --> 01:28.909
the professional golfer.

01:28.911 --> 01:30.244
Isn't he handsome?

01:30.246 --> 01:32.480
Lock up your daughters. He's single.

01:32.482 --> 01:33.814
- Mom.
- Come here, Ethan.

01:33.816 --> 01:35.049
Say hi to everyone.

01:35.051 --> 01:39.320
Martina? Stella? Oh, so good to see you!

01:39.322 --> 01:43.591
- And who is your lovely friend?
- Ethan, it's me, Shea.

01:43.593 --> 01:45.192
Shea?

01:45.194 --> 01:46.861
Little Shea with the
coke bottle glasses,

01:46.863 --> 01:49.630
acne, and dental headgear?

01:49.632 --> 01:53.200
Yes, puberty was not my friend.

01:53.202 --> 01:56.137
Nor were any actual people.

01:56.139 --> 01:57.671
Well, look at you now.

01:57.673 --> 01:59.840
Not that I'm looking.

01:59.842 --> 02:03.577
I mean, I am, but just
the regular amount.

02:03.579 --> 02:06.080
Hey, how about a round
of drinks on the house

02:06.082 --> 02:07.982
for my wonderful son?

02:07.984 --> 02:11.585
Wow, all I did was get the ketchup, Dad.

02:11.587 --> 02:12.753
Not you!

02:12.755 --> 02:13.854
Ethan!

02:13.856 --> 02:18.325
Hey, Mike. My brother
from another mother!

02:18.327 --> 02:21.195
And father.

02:21.197 --> 02:22.763
So what brings you to Seattle, Ethan?

02:22.765 --> 02:24.999
On my way to the Tokyo Pro-Am.

02:25.001 --> 02:26.066
The sponsors are putting me up

02:26.068 --> 02:27.368
for the night at the Four Seasons.

02:27.370 --> 02:28.469
The Four Seasons, Mike.

02:28.471 --> 02:31.906
That's all the seasons there are.

02:31.908 --> 02:33.174
I remember you when I fitted you

02:33.176 --> 02:34.909
for your first set of clubs.

02:34.911 --> 02:36.644
Only ten years old, and
you could already drive

02:36.646 --> 02:39.013
the ball 200 yards.

02:39.015 --> 02:41.215
I still have those clubs, Dad.

02:41.217 --> 02:44.085
You trying to make me cry?

02:44.087 --> 02:45.853
Well, a celebration is in order.

02:45.855 --> 02:47.621
I think we should move game night.

02:47.623 --> 02:49.056
I love game night.

02:49.058 --> 02:51.258
And me and you, Dad, we're
an unbeatable team.

02:51.260 --> 02:54.428
Perfect! We'll be partners!

02:54.430 --> 02:56.397
No reason not to be.

02:58.266 --> 03:00.000
Here's your stupid ketchup.

03:02.804 --> 03:05.806
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

03:09.972 --> 03:13.582
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

03:13.815 --> 03:16.117
My client cancelled so...

03:16.119 --> 03:19.186
Were you gonna eat that sugary cereal?

03:19.188 --> 03:22.490
How did you figure it out, detective?

03:22.492 --> 03:25.192
You specifically asked me
not to buy sugary things,

03:25.194 --> 03:26.727
so you could cut down on sugar.

03:26.729 --> 03:29.530
I only say that because
you get turned on

03:29.532 --> 03:33.701
when I pretend I'm going
to improve myself.

03:33.703 --> 03:36.003
Mike, I know what it's like to
give up something you love.

03:36.005 --> 03:38.806
I gave up smoking, which was
the hardest thing I've done

03:38.808 --> 03:43.878
and I pushed humans out of me.

03:43.880 --> 03:47.381
I hate when you win arguments
using your vagina.

03:47.383 --> 03:48.449
I'll get rid of it.

03:54.623 --> 03:56.690
I feel so alone.

03:58.994 --> 04:01.529
Do you think you're turning to cereal

04:01.531 --> 04:03.564
because when Ethan's
around your dad shows

04:03.566 --> 04:04.899
an obvious preference to him,

04:04.901 --> 04:06.534
and deep down you know
you need to confront him

04:06.536 --> 04:09.236
about the resentment you've
been harboring for 20 years?

04:09.238 --> 04:10.838
No.

04:12.841 --> 04:14.675
So you don't think there's
any sibling rivalry

04:14.677 --> 04:17.344
going on here at all?

04:17.346 --> 04:19.380
No.

04:19.382 --> 04:21.415
I wish my step-brother
would fail at something

04:21.416 --> 04:23.417
so I could be the good son.

04:23.419 --> 04:25.386
Does that make me a terrible person?

04:25.388 --> 04:27.855
Yes, yes, it does.

04:27.857 --> 04:30.624
Sweetie, there's stuff that I do

04:30.626 --> 04:33.160
in my therapy practice that might help.

04:33.162 --> 04:35.963
For example... we could role play,

04:35.965 --> 04:38.733
so I can show you that it's not
gonna be as hard as you think.

04:38.735 --> 04:39.934
And I'm going to do it

04:39.936 --> 04:43.037
just to show you what a
bad idea it would be.

04:45.674 --> 04:49.643
I'll be Bob and you say
what's in your heart.

04:49.645 --> 04:52.847
Okay, Dad...

04:52.849 --> 04:55.750
I loved having sex
with you this morning.

05:00.555 --> 05:01.722
Take it seriously.

05:01.724 --> 05:05.960
I can't. You know why? It's dumb.

05:05.962 --> 05:08.796
There's no wrong way to do this.

05:11.333 --> 05:15.236
Dad... you've always preferred Ethan,

05:15.238 --> 05:18.239
and you're a mean son of
a bitch with devil eyes.

05:19.474 --> 05:21.308
Why won't you take this seriously?

05:21.310 --> 05:22.543
Because, well, are we sure

05:22.545 --> 05:25.513
that therapy does anything?

05:28.450 --> 05:29.517
Say what now?

05:29.519 --> 05:31.118
Now you're upset. This is what happens

05:31.120 --> 05:34.088
when you express your feelings.

05:34.090 --> 05:37.391
Wow, you know what? I need some air.

05:37.393 --> 05:38.426
Shows what you know.

05:38.428 --> 05:41.028
Everyone needs air!

05:43.598 --> 05:45.633
Good one, Mike.

05:47.369 --> 05:49.070
I can't believe they let us win.

05:49.072 --> 05:51.238
I guess they wanted us to
feel good about ourselves.

05:51.240 --> 05:55.009
I mean, who do they think
they are, alcohol?

05:55.011 --> 05:56.177
If we're going to win fair and square,

05:56.179 --> 05:58.212
we need to work our
butts off practicing.

05:58.214 --> 06:00.147
That sounds awful, but...

06:00.149 --> 06:02.450
Okay, I'll get the weed.

06:02.452 --> 06:03.818
We can't practice high.

06:03.820 --> 06:04.919
Why not?

06:04.921 --> 06:06.921
As long as we also play the game high,

06:06.923 --> 06:08.489
we're golden.

06:08.491 --> 06:12.193
You should really know
that as a scientist.

